  "body": "We'd like to start thinking of how Status users can program smart contracts on smartphones, coding directly in solidity is out of the question but a intuitive \"lego-like\" blocks that you can snap together to produce smart contracts would be a fantastic start.\n\nThe Google Blockly GUI seems like a great candidate but the GUI looks a little .. dated. \nIt would be great if we could reskin/reimagine what this would look like, in the Status look-and-feel.\n\nAn example of such an effort can be found here\nhttp://etherscripter.com/\n\nOur version should behave very similar to how Etherscripter does in terms of snapping on inputs and outputs, expanding their sizes to fit.\n\nPinch in/out to zoom in and out of the designer space\nTouch off blocks to pan around designer space\n\nAn example would be creating a multi-sig wallet or creating an escrow contract. Creating their own custom commands/requests inside Status.\n\nâ”†Issue is synchronized with this [Asana task](https://app.asana.com/0/193967741406403/193974073352370)\n",
