    "body": "Hello, Jarrad! i had been sketching a little on the weekend and here's what i came up with.\nWhat i thing about this thing is that it looks viable but it has to be done really good in terms of technical implementation and UX. I mean it should zoom in and out automatically in the right moment, auto-scroll left and right when drag and drop, and much more UX stuff we have to test and research and update and so on. \n\nIt feels like for this UI there's a tiny step between the \"wow, it's nice\" and \"why the hell should i use this, i'd better write code\"\n\n![ios_blocky](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3115606/19232894/175d7388-8eeb-11e6-883d-fa6a1d3fef0c.png)\n",
